text: Tuckabum Creek is a stream in the U.S. states of Alabama and Mississippi. Tuckabum is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean either (sources vary) "first" or "stream bed", but the meaning can not be known with certainty. Variant names are "Tickabum Creek", "Tuckabunne Creek", "Tuckaburne Creek", and "Tuckalum Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Alabama Category:Bodies of water of Choctaw County, Alabama Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Lauderdale County, Mississippi
title: Tuckabum Creek
